events.description: The Franks are defeated by the Burgundians in the Battle of Vézeronce.
events.html: • 524 – The Franks are defeated by the Burgundians in the Battle of Vézeronce.[1]

events.description: In the Battle of Fontenay-en-Puisaye, forces led by Charles the Bald and Louis the German defeat the armies of Lothair I of Italy and Pepin II of Aquitaine.
events.html: • 841 – In the Battle of Fontenay-en-Puisaye, forces led by Charles the Bald and Louis the German defeat the armies of Lothair I of Italy and Pepin II of Aquitaine.[2]

events.description: War of Saint Sabas: In the Battle of Acre, the Venetians defeat a larger Genoese fleet sailing to relieve Acre.
events.html: • 1258 – War of Saint Sabas: In the Battle of Acre, the Venetians defeat a larger Genoese fleet sailing to relieve Acre.

events.description: At the Diet of Augsburg the Augsburg Confession is presented to the Holy Roman Emperor by the Lutheran princes and Electors of Germany.
events.html: • 1530 – At the Diet of Augsburg the Augsburg Confession is presented to the Holy Roman Emperor by the Lutheran princes and Electors of Germany.

events.description: Spanish forces fail to retake Jamaica at the Battle of Rio Nuevo during the Anglo-Spanish War.
events.html: • 1658 – Spanish forces fail to retake Jamaica at the Battle of Rio Nuevo during the Anglo-Spanish War.

events.description: Venetian Elena Cornaro Piscopia is the first woman awarded a doctorate of philosophy when she graduates from the University of Padua.
events.html: • 1678 – Venetian Elena Cornaro Piscopia is the first woman awarded a doctorate of philosophy when she graduates from the University of Padua.

events.description: Maria Theresa is crowned Queen of Hungary.
events.html: • 1741 – Maria Theresa is crowned Queen of Hungary.

events.description: Gavriil Pribylov discovers St. George Island of the Pribilof Islands in the Bering Sea.
events.html: • 1786 – Gavriil Pribylov discovers St. George Island of the Pribilof Islands in the Bering Sea.

events.description: Virginia becomes the tenth state to ratify the United States Constitution.
events.html: • 1788 – Virginia becomes the tenth state to ratify the United States Constitution.

events.description: A photograph of the June Days uprising becomes the first known instance of photojournalism.
events.html: • 1848 – A photograph of the June Days uprising becomes the first known instance of photojournalism.

events.description: American Indian Wars: Battle of the Little Bighorn: 300 men of the U.S. 7th Cavalry Regiment under Lieutenant Colonel George Armstrong Custer are wiped out by 5,000 Lakota, Cheyenne and Arapaho, led by Sitting Bull and Crazy Horse.
events.html: • 1876 – American Indian Wars: Battle of the Little Bighorn: 300 men of the U.S. 7th Cavalry Regiment under Lieutenant Colonel George Armstrong Custer are wiped out by 5,000 Lakota, Cheyenne and Arapaho, led by Sitting Bull and Crazy Horse.

events.description: The Taoist monk Wang Yuanlu discovers the Dunhuang manuscripts, a cache of ancient texts that are of great historical and religious significance, in the Mogao Caves of Dunhuang, China.
events.html: • 1900 – The Taoist monk Wang Yuanlu discovers the Dunhuang manuscripts, a cache of ancient texts that are of great historical and religious significance, in the Mogao Caves of Dunhuang, China.

events.description: Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania millionaire Harry Thaw shoots and kills prominent architect Stanford White.
events.html: • 1906 – Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania millionaire Harry Thaw shoots and kills prominent architect Stanford White.

events.description: The United States Congress passes the Mann Act, which prohibits interstate transport of women or girls for "immoral purposes"; the ambiguous language would be used to selectively prosecute people for years to come.
events.html: • 1910 – The United States Congress passes the Mann Act, which prohibits interstate transport of women or girls for "immoral purposes"; the ambiguous language would be used to selectively prosecute people for years to come.

events.description: Igor Stravinsky's ballet The Firebird is premiered in Paris, bringing him to prominence as a composer.
events.html: • 1910 – Igor Stravinsky's ballet The Firebird is premiered in Paris, bringing him to prominence as a composer.

events.description: American Civil War veterans begin arriving at the Great Reunion of 1913.
events.html: • 1913 – American Civil War veterans begin arriving at the Great Reunion of 1913.

events.description: Colombia–Soviet Union relations are established.
events.html: • 1935 – Colombia–Soviet Union relations are established.

events.description: Dr. Douglas Hyde is inaugurated as the first President of Ireland.
events.html: • 1938 – Dr. Douglas Hyde is inaugurated as the first President of Ireland.

events.description: World War II: The French armistice with Nazi Germany comes into effect.
events.html: • 1940 – World War II: The French armistice with Nazi Germany comes into effect.

events.description: World War II: The Continuation War between the Soviet Union and Finland, supported by Nazi Germany, began.
events.html: • 1941 – World War II: The Continuation War between the Soviet Union and Finland, supported by Nazi Germany, began.[3]

events.description: The Holocaust and World War II: Jews in the Częstochowa Ghetto in Poland stage an uprising against the Nazis.
events.html: • 1943 – The Holocaust and World War II: Jews in the Częstochowa Ghetto in Poland stage an uprising against the Nazis.

events.description: The left-wing German Jewish exile Arthur Goldstein is murdered in Auschwitz.
events.html: • 1943 – The left-wing German Jewish exile Arthur Goldstein is murdered in Auschwitz.

events.description: World War II: The Battle of Tali-Ihantala, the largest battle ever fought in the Nordic countries, begins.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: The Battle of Tali-Ihantala, the largest battle ever fought in the Nordic countries, begins.

events.description: World War II: United States Navy and British Royal Navy ships bombard Cherbourg to support United States Army units engaged in the Battle of Cherbourg.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: United States Navy and British Royal Navy ships bombard Cherbourg to support United States Army units engaged in the Battle of Cherbourg.

events.description: The final page of the comic Krazy Kat is published, exactly two months after its author George Herriman died.
events.html: • 1944 – The final page of the comic Krazy Kat is published, exactly two months after its author George Herriman died.

events.description: The Diary of a Young Girl (better known as The Diary of Anne Frank) is published.
events.html: • 1947 – The Diary of a Young Girl (better known as The Diary of Anne Frank) is published.

entities.name: The Diary of a Young Girl

events.description: The United States Congress passes the Displaced Persons Act to allow World War II refugees to immigrate to the United States above quota restrictions.
events.html: • 1948 – The United States Congress passes the Displaced Persons Act to allow World War II refugees to immigrate to the United States above quota restrictions.[4]

events.description: The Korean War begins with the invasion of South Korea by North Korea.
events.html: • 1950 – The Korean War begins with the invasion of South Korea by North Korea.

events.description: Cold War: Two cryptographers working for the United States National Security Agency left for vacation to Mexico, and from there defected to the Soviet Union.
events.html: • 1960 – Cold War: Two cryptographers working for the United States National Security Agency left for vacation to Mexico, and from there defected to the Soviet Union.

events.description: Mozambique achieves independence from Portugal.
events.html: • 1975 – Mozambique achieves independence from Portugal.

events.description: Prime Minister Indira Gandhi declares a state of internal emergency in India.
events.html: • 1975 – Prime Minister Indira Gandhi declares a state of internal emergency in India.

events.description: Missouri Governor Kit Bond issues an executive order rescinding the Extermination Order, formally apologizing on behalf of the state of Missouri for the suffering it had caused to members of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints.
events.html: • 1976 – Missouri Governor Kit Bond issues an executive order rescinding the Extermination Order, formally apologizing on behalf of the state of Missouri for the suffering it had caused to members of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints.

entities.name: The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints

events.description: The rainbow flag representing gay pride is flown for the first time during the San Francisco Gay Freedom Day Parade.
events.html: • 1978 – The rainbow flag representing gay pride is flown for the first time during the San Francisco Gay Freedom Day Parade.

events.description: Microsoft is restructured to become an incorporated business in its home state of Washington.
events.html: • 1981 – Microsoft is restructured to become an incorporated business in its home state of Washington.

events.description: The breakup of Yugoslavia begins when Slovenia and Croatia declare their independence from Yugoslavia.
events.html: • 1991 – The breakup of Yugoslavia begins when Slovenia and Croatia declare their independence from Yugoslavia.

events.description: Space Shuttle Columbia launches on STS-50, the first shuttle mission to carry Extended Duration Orbiter hardware.
events.html: • 1992 – Space Shuttle Columbia launches on STS-50, the first shuttle mission to carry Extended Duration Orbiter hardware.[5]

events.description: Kim Campbell is sworn in as the first female Prime Minister of Canada.
events.html: • 1993 – Kim Campbell is sworn in as the first female Prime Minister of Canada.

events.description: The Khobar Towers bombing in Saudi Arabia kills 19 U.S. servicemen.
events.html: • 1996 – The Khobar Towers bombing in Saudi Arabia kills 19 U.S. servicemen.

events.html: • 1996 – American rapper Jay-Z releases his debut album, Reasonable Doubt. [6]

events.description: An uncrewed Progress spacecraft collides with the Russian space station Mir.
events.html: • 1997 – An uncrewed Progress spacecraft collides with the Russian space station Mir.

events.html: • 2022 – The prime minister of Bangladesh, Sheikh Hasina inaugurates the longest bridge of Bangladesh, Padma Bridge.[8]
